com.serena.dmclient.objects
Interface PrimingRelationship

All Superinterfaces:
DimensionsObject
public interface PrimingRelationship
extends DimensionsObject

Represents a Dimensions priming relationship.

Priming is the process of creating a request based on the contents of another request. The values of a pre-specified set of attributes are copied from the base request to their corresponding attributes in the new request. The mapping between the attributes (which base request attributes will be copied to which attributes new request attributes), is set by using the methods of this interface.

Notes on priming the system attribute pcms_chdoc_detail_desc (Detail Description):

  1. If a mapping for pcms_chdoc_detail_desc is not specified, it is assumed that the change document detail description is to be primed from the detail description of the base request.
  2. You cannot prime a user-defined attribute from pcms_chdoc_detail_desc, but the reverse is permitted.
